.Dd $Mdocdate$
.Dt checkbatt 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm checkbatt
.Nd displays an alert if the battery is low
.Sh DESCRIPTION
A first alert is displayed from a level of 20%

A critical second alert is displayed at 10%. This leaves a
short time for user to turn off or plug in his
computer.

This script is supposed to be called regularly via a
cron job.

.Bd -literal
*/5 * * * * /home/foo/bin/checkbatt >/dev/null 2>&1
.Ed

.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr apm 8
.Xr dunst 1
.Xr crontab 1
